		     NOTE FROM SEEDER RuBBaDuB9202:

This program is 100% bug & virus free, and I am currently using the program,
myself, on Windows XP. I, personally, have not tested the VISTA version that
is included. Please comment to verify if the VISTA version runs without problems.
				 ENJOY!!!

  ******************************************************************
  ******************************************************************
  ******************************************************************

      			     INSTALLATION:

In order to install ZoneAlarm Internet Security Suite, flawlessly,
Please follow these directions:
__________________________________________________________________

BEFORE INSTALLING, TURN OF ALL INTERNET ACCESS TO PREVENT ZONEALARM FROM
DETECTING YOUR SHARED SERIAL!


	1)Run setup application....

	2)Providing e-mail address is optional...

	3)Use one of the serials [at the bottom of the page] to register...

	4)After installing, you will need to disable automatic updates, 
	  so Zonealarm does not detect the pirated program.
	  To do so, please follow these directions:


Part 1:	a) Open the main ZoneAlarm application.
	b) On left side of application\&#039;s window, click \"Overview\"
	c) In the \"Overview\" section, click the \"Preferences\" tab, at the 
	top-right (Under \"Help\" icon)
	d) Where it says \"Check for product updates\", change the selection
	 FROM \"Automatically\" TO \"Manually\"

Part 2:	e) On left side of application\&#039;s window, click \"Program Control\"
	f) Once \"Program Control\" is opened, Click the middle tab (at the 
	   top), named \"Programs\"
	g) On the list of programs, find \"Zonealarm Updating Client\"
	h) To the right of \"Zonealarm Updating Client\", find the question
	   mark icons. Click on them to change them all to \"block\", shown 
	   by the red \"X\" icons.

5) Zonealarm should be working!!!
	-To double-check, click on the \"Overview\" tab, on the left side of
	 the window.
	-In the \"Overview\" section,click the \"Product Info\" tab, at the top.
	-Under \"Product Info\", look at the \"Support and Update Information\"
	 section and
	 verify that the product does not expire in the near future. It should
	 say something like \"51570 days\"
